      "lesson title": "Testing AI Systems: Why Traditional QA Fails",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Traditional software testing relies on predictable, repeatable outcomes, where the same input always produces the same output. AI systems behave very differently, generating responses that can vary each time, making conventional pass/fail testing methods largely ineffective. In this lesson, you will explore why the deterministic approaches used in standard QA processes struggle to keep pace with the probabilistic nature of AI. We will look at practical examples that highlight where traditional testing breaks down, and begin to build an understanding of what a more suitable testing approach might look like. By the end, you will have a clearer picture of the unique challenges involved in testing AI systems and why new thinking is needed in this space.",
      "status": "draft",
