          "slidetitle": "Testing AI: A New Challenge",
          "subtitle": "Why old methods fall short here",
          "slidecontent": "• Traditional QA assumes software behaves the same way every time it runs\n• AI systems are probabilistic, meaning identical inputs can produce different outputs\n• Old pass/fail checklists simply do not apply\n• Deterministic testing methods were built for rule-based code, not learned behaviour\n• A spell-checker either works or it does not, but an AI writing tool might be right, wrong, or somewhere in between\n• This gap between old methods and new systems is exactly what this course addresses"
