          "subtitle": "Why AI outputs vary each time",
          "slidecontent": "• AI systems use probability and randomness to generate responses, so identical inputs rarely produce identical outputs\n• Unlike a calculator, no guaranteed fixed answer\n• Temperature settings, sampling methods, and model state all influence what gets returned each time\n• Running the same test twice can produce two completely different, yet equally valid, results\n• This breaks the core assumption that traditional QA relies on\n• Deterministic testing tools expect one correct output to check against, making them poorly suited for systems that are designed to vary"
